<subSubSection id="C32B6553FF893A7CBBD2FB156318BA34" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8E36D8FF893A7CBBD2FB156318BA34" blockId="7.[151,1437,1230,2025]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF893A7CBBD2FB156149BBE1" bold="true" box="[151,273,1230,1255]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Best distinguished by the R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CB917FB066202BBED" box="[594,602,1245,1259]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CB926FB066232BBED" box="[611,618,1245,1259]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="5.0">5</number>
fork distal to the position of the M 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CB8B9FB066459BBED" box="[1020,1025,1245,1259]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBF49FB06644DBBED" box="[1036,1045,1245,1259]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="2.0">2</number>
fork, shorter than the length of R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBED1FB0665C4BBED" box="[1428,1436,1245,1259]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="4.0">4</number>
(
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF893A7CBBDAFB2E60AEBA08" box="[159,246,1269,1294]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBB93FB2E60AEBA08" box="[214,246,1269,1294]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
); shape of the male cercus being incurved apically, longer than epandrium in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF893A7CBE4BFB2E653ABA08" box="[1294,1378,1269,1294]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBE00FB2D653ABA08" box="[1349,1378,1270,1294]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
) and phallus with two posterolateral pointed projections (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF893A7CB99AFAC2636BBA34" box="[735,819,1305,1330]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CB856FAC1636BBA34" box="[787,819,1306,1330]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32B6553FF893A72BB82FAE66228BE46" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="218" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8E36D8FF893A72BB82FAE66228BE46" blockId="7.[151,1437,1230,2025]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1437,151,794]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="218" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF893A7CBB82FAE66109BA50" bold="true" box="[199,337,1341,1366]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">Description</emphasis>
. Male (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF893A7CBAF6FAE66254BA50" box="[435,524,1341,1366]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBAA8FAE66254BA50" box="[493,524,1341,1366]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF893A7CB960FAE6623CBA50" bold="true" box="[549,612,1341,1366]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">Head</emphasis>
. Dark brown to black, antenna and mouthparts yellow with all setae whitish; ocellar triangle with 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBAA5FAB961B6BA7C" box="[480,494,1378,1402]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of proclinate setae; anterior ocellus larger. Eyes iridescent black, very narrowly separated on face which bears fine reclinate setulae. Frons with 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CB8CDFA5D63EABA98" box="[904,946,1414,1438]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
setulae; one pair of distinct vertical setae contiguous with uniseriate smaller postocular setae; occiput bearing scattered fine hairs. Clypeus with rather dense short downwardly directed pile. Proboscis slightly curved with setae yellow. Antenna with scape and pedicel bearing distinct short dorsal setulae; postpedicel about 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CB846FA2A637CB90C" box="[771,804,1521,1546]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X as long as wide, stylus ~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBF1AFA2964DAB90C" box="[1119,1154,1522,1546]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="0.8">0.8</number>
X as long as postpedicel. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF893A7CBBD2F9CE60A8B928" bold="true" box="[151,240,1557,1582]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF893A7CBBBBF9CE6109B928" box="[254,337,1557,1582]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBA77F9CE6109B928" box="[306,337,1557,1582]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). Elongate, slightly arched ventrally; dorsum yellow, except brownish on mediotergite and median stripe on prothoracic collar; antepronotum with anterior margin almost straight; scutum with yellow setae, very small and fine except 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBAD6F98561F9B970" box="[403,417,1630,1654]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
notopleural. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF893A7CB97DF9866228B970" bold="true" box="[568,624,1629,1654]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF893A7CB9C4F986628EB970" box="[641,726,1629,1654]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CB9F2F986628EB970" box="[695,726,1629,1654]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). Whitish yellow. C 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CB8FBF9856390B970" box="[958,968,1630,1654]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CB8ADF9856452B970" box="[1000,1034,1630,1654]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.4">1.4</number>
X longer than distance between C 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBED7F98565C4B970" box="[1426,1436,1630,1654]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
and C2, 
<date id="FF8F1018FF893A7CBBB2F95A6142B99C" box="[247,282,1665,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">6X</date>
as long as wide. F 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBAB1F95961A6B99C" box="[500,510,1666,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CB95BF9596267B99C" box="[542,575,1666,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.1">1.1</number>
X as long as C1, 
<date id="FF8F1018FF893A7CB842F9596372B99C" box="[775,810,1666,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">4X</date>
as long as wide. Femoral formula 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBFF2F95A649DB99C" box="[1207,1221,1665,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="7.0">7</number>
/ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBF8AF95A654EB99C" box="[1231,1302,1665,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="16.5" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="16.0">16–17</number>
/ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBE65F95A6571B99C" box="[1312,1321,1665,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBE7FF95A65D9B99C" box="[1338,1409,1665,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="14.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.0">14–15</number>
/ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBECEF95A65C0B99C" box="[1419,1432,1665,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="5.0">5</number>
; denticles confined to distal 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBA89F97D61AAB9B8" box="[460,498,1702,1726]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="0.7">0.7</number>
, 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBABBF97D6254B9B8" box="[510,524,1702,1726]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="2.0">2</number>
rows linear, black, without distal discontinuity, converging distally but divergent at tip. T 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBBBCF911615BB9E4" box="[249,259,1738,1762]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBA6DF9126113B9E4" box="[296,331,1737,1762]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="0.6">0.6</number>
X as long as F 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBABBF9116251B9E4" box="[510,521,1738,1762]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
, evenly curved, ventral face shallowly concave; with 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBF3BF91164D4B9E4" box="[1150,1164,1738,1762]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="2.0">2</number>
rows of 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBFBCF9126567B9E4" box="[1273,1343,1737,1762]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="16.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="15.0">15–18</number>
sharply pointed spinose setae ventrally; dorsal ciliation of decumbent short pale setulae, denser distally; slight apicoventral extension on T 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBA04F8C96113B82C" box="[321,331,1810,1834]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
bearing strong apical spine. Mid and hind legs slender with fine setae but T 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBFE4F8C964F5B82C" box="[1185,1197,1810,1834]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="3.0">3</number>
with ‘comb’ of short setae posteroapically. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF893A7CBADCF8EE6182B848" bold="true" box="[409,474,1845,1870]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">Wing</emphasis>
(
