<emphasis id="B945EACAFF893A7CBF6EF87264F8B8C4" bold="true" box="[1067,1184,1961,1986]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF893A7CBFEBF8726568B8C4" box="[1198,1328,1961,1986]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">Figs 25, 27</figureCitation>
). Tergites 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBBD2F80A60FDB8EF" box="[151,165,2001,2025]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBB9EF80A60B1B8EE" box="[219,233,2001,2024]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="7.0">7</number>
and sternites yellowish, tergites 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CB93EF80B62FDB8EF" box="[635,677,2000,2025]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="4.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="2.0">2–6</number>
and 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CB9A7F80A62A8B8EF" box="[738,752,2001,2025]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="8.0">8</number>
brownish with distinct setae on posterior margin; tergite 
<number id="3DF924FFFF893A7CBE3DF80A65DEB8EF" box="[1400,1414,2001,2025]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="8.0">8</number>
shorter than sternite 
<number id="3DF924FFFF863A73BA3BF8B661D6B883" box="[382,398,1901,1925]" pageId="8" pageNumber="217" value="8.0">8</number>
. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF863A73BADFF8B76245B883" bold="true" box="[410,541,1900,1925]" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Brownish. Cercus narrow, curved up distally with rounded apex (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF863A73BE4EF8B765D7B883" box="[1291,1423,1900,1925]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">Figs 27, 28</figureCitation>
); left and right cerci closely approximated anterodorsally (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF863A73B852F84A6334B8AF" box="[791,876,1937,1962]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF863A73B809F84A6334B8AF" box="[844,876,1937,1961]" pageId="8" pageNumber="217" value="29.0">29</number>
</figureCitation>
). Epandrium wide, subrectangular in lateral view, with strong setae on outer face at apex (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF863A73B91DF86E62F4B8CB" box="[600,684,1973,1998]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF863A73B9C9F86E62F4B8CB" box="[652,684,1973,1997]" pageId="8" pageNumber="217" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
). Surstylus (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF863A73B87DF86E63D2B8CB" box="[824,906,1973,1998]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF863A73B828F86E63D2B8CB" box="[877,906,1973,1997]" pageId="8" pageNumber="217" value="29.0">29</number>
</figureCitation>
) bilobed, with spine-like setae on inner face of outer lobe. Hypandrium rather rounded in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF863A73B87EF80263CBB8F7" box="[827,915,2009,2034]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF863A73B830F80263CBB8F7" box="[885,915,2009,2033]" pageId="8" pageNumber="217" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
), not markedly inflated, with distinct setae; gonocoxal apodeme confined to anterior margin of hypandrium, lacking narrow process. Subepandrial sclerite concave on anterior margin, two short finger-like posterior processes with long setae at apex (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF873A72BF99FF67656BBFD2" box="[1244,1331,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF873A72BE56FF67656BBFD2" box="[1299,1331,188,212]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" value="29.0">29</number>
</figureCitation>
). Phallus sclerotized with two posterolateral pointed projections, extending well beyond hypandrium apex, apical membranous area covered with minute dark spicules (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF873A72B9B4FEDF631DBE1A" box="[753,837,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF873A72B860FEDF631DBE1A" box="[805,837,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme absent. 
